description._content: Group of men and women posing in front of part of Woodford House, the private sandstone residence of Alfred Fairfax from 1868. Formerly an inn, with parts of building dating to 1830s. Known as Woodford Academy since 1907, when it became a private school for boys. Possibly an RAHS excursion. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains Excursions', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
